    • Method Detail

      • registerEntityType

        void registerEntityType​(String typeName,
                        String textureHandle,
                        Class<? extends Entity> entityType)
        Register a new entity type by name.

        This method attempts to build a Supplier function out of the provided class object. The Supplier function will be called once to test its functionality.

        Parameters:
        typeName - the name of the entity type
        textureHandle - the texture handle to use as an icon for this type
        entityType - the class object of the entity type
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if an argument is null
        IllegalArgumentException - if the built Supplier function could not instantiate an entity
        ElementExistsException - if the name is already used

      • registerEntityType

        void registerEntityType​(String typeName,
                        String textureHandle,
                        Supplier<? extends Entity> entityFactory)
        Register a new entity type by name.

        The entityFactory will be called once to test its functionality.

        Parameters:
        typeName - the name of the entity type
        textureHandle - the texture handle to use as an icon for this type
        entityFactory - supplier function to create new instances of this entity type
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if an argument is null
        IllegalArgumentException - if the entityFactory could not instantiate an entity
        ElementExistsException - if the name is already used
